    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given regulatory precedent for ambient static testing under ASTM F1717 and the explicitly static, single-condition scope of the COU. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference <10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for predicting ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
